---
/**
 * SoA vs AoS memory layout animation.
 * Shows which bytes are "hot" (used) vs "cold" (wasted) in each layout
 * when only accessing position (x, y, z) fields.
 */
---

<figure class="soa-aos">
  <div class="layout-grid">
    <!-- AoS layout -->
    <div class="layout-col">
      <div class="layout-title">Array of Structures (AoS)</div>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <text x="160" y="14" class="section-label">Memory layout (one cache line = 2 particles)</text>

        <!-- Particle 0 -->
        {["x","y","z","vx","vy","vz","m","q"].map((f, i) => (
          <g>
            <rect x={5 + i * 38} y="24" width="36" height="22" rx="2"
                  class={i < 3 ? "field hot" : "field cold"} />
            <text x={23 + i * 38} y="39" class="field-label">{f}</text>
          </g>
        ))}
        <text x="160" y="58" class="particle-label">particle[0]</text>

        <!-- Particle 1 -->
        {["x","y","z","vx","vy","vz","m","q"].map((f, i) => (
          <g>
            <rect x={5 + i * 38} y="65" width="36" height="22" rx="2"
                  class={i < 3 ? "field hot" : "field cold"} />
            <text x={23 + i * 38} y="80" class="field-label">{f}</text>
          </g>
        ))}
        <text x="160" y="99" class="particle-label">particle[1]</text>

        <text x="160" y="118" class="stat bad">6/16 fields used per cache line → 37.5%</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- SoA layout -->
    <div class="layout-col">
      <div class="layout-title">Structure of Arrays (SoA)</div>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <text x="160" y="14" class="section-label">Memory layout (one cache line = 16 x values)</text>

        <!-- x array -->
        {Array.from({ length: 16 }).map((_, i) => (
          <rect x={5 + i * 19.4} y="24" width="17.5" height="22" rx="2" class="field hot" />
        ))}
        <text x="160" y="58" class="particle-label">x[0] x[1] x[2] x[3] x[4] ... x[15] — all used ✓</text>

        <!-- vx array -->
        {Array.from({ length: 16 }).map((_, i) => (
          <rect x={5 + i * 19.4} y="65" width="17.5" height="22" rx="2" class="field cold" />
        ))}
        <text x="160" y="99" class="particle-label">vx[0] ... vx[15] — separate cache line, not loaded</text>

        <text x="160" y="118" class="stat good">16/16 fields used per cache line → 100%</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
  <figcaption>When updating only positions (x, y, z), AoS wastes bandwidth loading velocity, mass, and charge. SoA keeps each field contiguous — every byte in the cache line is useful.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .soa-aos {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .soa-aos figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .layout-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 650px) {
    .layout-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .layout-col svg {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }
  .layout-title {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    color: #333;
  }
  .section-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 7.5px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #888;
  }
  .field {
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .field.hot {
    fill: #c8e6c9;
    stroke: #4caf50;
  }
  .field.cold {
    fill: #ffcdd2;
    stroke: #e57373;
  }
  .field-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #444;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .particle-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 6.5px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #888;
  }
  .stat {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .stat.good { fill: #2e7d32; }
  .stat.bad { fill: #c62828; }
</style>
